00:01:36,220 --> 00:01:37,940
鲁思 发生了什么...
Oh, Ruth, what on earth ...

6
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,670
刘易斯 我的东西
Oh, Lewis! All my things!

7
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:43,700
- 刘易斯 - 女士们
- Lewis! - Ladies.

8
00:01:52,270 --> 00:01:57,210
《借镜杀人》


9
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:04,720
您的茶 夫人
Your tea, madam.

10
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:09,019
他们理所当然地将火灾归咎于线路故障
Natural, they all put the fire down to a faulty wire,

11
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:10,829
但我清楚自己看到了什么
but I know what I saw.

12
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,589
有个男人 我现在还能想起他
There was a man. I can see him now.

13
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,410
他...他悄悄穿过走廊
He was...was stilling across the hallway.

14
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:17,449
他长什么样 鲁思
How would you describe him, Ruth?

15
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:21,629
- 邪恶 邪恶至极 - 我知道了
- Wicked. Quite, quite wicked. - I see.

16
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,979
当然 卡莉・路易斯说我是在做梦
Of course, Carrie Louise says that I dreamed it all,

17
00:02:23,990 --> 00:02:28,480
但我姐姐从来都不愿意听不愉快的真相
but my sister never had any time for unpalatable truths.

18
00:02:29,610 --> 00:02:32,450
简 你认为有人能猜出
Do you think anyone could possibly guess, Jane,

19
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:35,620
你我几乎同龄吗
that you and I are practically the same age?

20
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:37,479
肯定不会
Not for a moment, I'm sure.

21
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:40,779
我嘛 每分钟都在衰老
I'm afraid, you see, I look every minute of my age.

22
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:42,180
才不会
No!

23
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,789
这起火灾是何时发生的
When was it, this fire?

24
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,120
六周前
Six weeks ago.

25
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,029
我刚从纽约飞来与受托人见面
I'd just flown in from New York for a meeting of the Trustees.

26
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:53,799
卡莉・路易斯的丈夫肯定看见了什么
Surely Carrie Louise's husband must have seen something?

27
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:58,159
刘易斯满眼都是他亲爱的妻子和她的事业
Lewis only has eyes for his dear wife and her blessed cause.

28
00:02:58,170 --> 00:02:59,809
她还在追求自己的事业吗
She's still keeping up with her causes?

29
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:01,670
太阳可不会打西边出来
Does the sun rise in the morning?

30
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:04,430
一般来说 一个年轻姑娘做这件事很时尚
Naturally, such thing is fashionable when one's a young girl.

31
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:06,439
我记得你当时想做一名修女
You were off to be a nun, I believe.

32
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:09,980
是 很有可能 但婚姻拴住了我
Yes. Very possibly. But marriage knocks sense into one,

33
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:13,570
天知道自从卡莉・路易斯结婚后
and God knows Carrie Louise has had plenty of practice

34
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:16,850
她付出了多少努力
ever since she threw herself at that luringly glump.

35
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:21,000
她第一任丈夫 古尔布兰德森先生
Her first husband, Mr. Gulbrandsen,

36
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:23,289
是个慈善家吧
He was something of a philanthropyst, wasn't he?

37
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:27,400
又结了两次婚 她还在靠他的遗产生活
And two husbands later, she is still living of his inheritance.

38
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,990
现在她又瞄上了新目标
And she's supered herself with this latest cause.

39
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:32,519
罪犯们
Criminals.

40
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:36,120
她以为自己能和他们"做点什么"
She imagines she can "do something" with them.

41
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:39,549
所以 他们来了 在她花园尽头
So, there they are, all living it up in a so-called

42
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:42,669
所谓的"改造工厂"里工作生活
"Reform Facility" at the bottom of her garden.

43
00:03:42,669 --> 00:03:47,250
- 你担心的就是这个吗 - 我不知道
- And this is what you afraid of? - I don't know.

44
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:51,860
每次我和她在一起 我感觉总有个人在她周围
All the time I was with her, I felt this-this presence around her.

45
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:54,670
然后...她书房的大火
And then... that fire in her study.

46
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,789
那座房子里的某个人想要伤害我姐姐
Someone in that house wishes my sister harm.

47
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:02,289
- 我敢说这一切听上去很偏激 - 不
- And I dare say this all sounds quite mad to you. - Oh, no.

48
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,680
- 你相信我吗 - 我相信你的判断
- You believe me? - I trust your conviction.

49
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:07,459
没有什么事能让你惊奇 对吧 简
Nothing has ever surprised you, has it, Jane?

50
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:09,990
因为你总是做最坏的打算
Because you always think the worst.

51
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,709
最坏的结果通常会发生
The worst is so often true.

52
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:14,330
那你会尽快去吧
Then you'll go? As soon as you can?

53
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:25,539
你记不记得她和古尔布兰德森
Do you remember how she and Gulbrandsen

54
00:04:25,550 --> 00:04:27,730
多么想要一个自己的孩子
longed for a child of their own?

55
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,639
他们不是最终收养了一个吗
Didn't they adopt in the end?

56
00:04:29,650 --> 00:04:31,920
我见过那孩子 非常漂亮的女孩
I think I met the child. A very pretty girl.

57
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:35,970
是的 吉娜 一个迷人的小可爱
Yes. Gina. A bewitching little thing.

58
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:39,589
然后 如你所料 没过多久
Then, as so often happens, not long after,

59
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,060
卡莉・路易斯发现自己怀孕了
Carrie Louise found herself pregnant.

60
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:45,209
通常 人们不会善待养子
Normally, it's hard lines on the adopted child,

61
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,820
但他们不同
but not in their case.

62
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:50,909
卡莉・路易斯生怕自己偏心
Carrie Louise was so anxious not to make the difference between them two

63
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:53,029
所以米尔德里德出世之后
that when Mildred came along,

64
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,580
任何事她都偏心小吉娜
if anything, she tended to over-indulge the little Gina,

65
00:04:56,980 --> 00:05:00,610
把她的亲生孩子晾在一边
while her natural child was left to fan herself.

66
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:04,520
可怜的米尔德里德 从未得到过母亲的爱
Poor Mildred. She never stood a chance.

67
00:05:15,090 --> 00:05:17,940
- 你好 - 你好
- Hello. - Oh! Hello.

68
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:20,610
这旅行袋真漂亮
Oh, what a nice trim bag.

69
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:21,719
您一定是...
You must be ...

70
00:05:21,730 --> 00:05:24,253
一号站台下一班列车
The next train on platform one 

71
00:05:24,254 --> 00:05:27,619
四点五十从帕丁顿开出
is the 4:50 from Paddington.

72
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,489
明天到达小佩维雷尔
All stations to Little Peverell tomorrow.

73
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,179
您一定是简姑妈
I said you must be Aunt Jane.

74
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:33,910
- 你一定是吉娜 - 您怎么知道
- And you must be Gina. - How did you guess?

75
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:36,940
不说也知道 走吧
Don't answer that. Come on.

76
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:49,940
入此地者将重获希望


77
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:04,909
这一定是那个著名的工厂
This must be the famous facility.

78
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:07,650
真是不可救药
Incorrigible.

79
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:10,880
- 你说谁 亲爱的 - 当然是他们
- Who, dear? - Well, them, of course.

80
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:21,450
妈妈
Mommy!

81
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:25,990
简
Jane!

82
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:30,639
我亲爱的卡莉・路易斯 你好吗
My dear Carrie Louise. How are you?

83
00:06:30,650 --> 00:06:33,580
身体老了 但还是一如既往的固执
The flesh is weak, but the spirit's as stubborn as ever.

84
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:35,820
你喝茶吗
Would you take tea?

85
00:06:35,910 --> 00:06:37,679
我一直站着喝
I always take mine standing up,

86
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:40,260
不然就再也站不起来了 你说呢
or otherwise one would seat around forever, don't you think?

87
00:06:40,350 --> 00:06:43,470
请允许我介绍刘易斯
Allow me to introduce Lewis ...

88
00:06:44,220 --> 00:06:48,060
我亲爱的丈夫和部落的酋长
treasured husband and chief of my tribe.

89
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,160
- 嗨 - 你好啊
- Ow. - How do you do?

90
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,699
业余爱好 为爱献身
Amateur dramatics. The things we do for love.

91
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:55,050
我觉得你看起来很勇猛
I think you look quite fierce.

92
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:58,700
- 你说呢 亲爱的 - 我不喜欢这种事
- Don't you, dear? - I have no head for such matters.

93
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:00,980
我女儿 米尔德里德
My daughter. Mildred.

94
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:03,860
真高兴终于见到你了
How very nice to meet you after this long while.

95
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,280
彼此彼此
Likewise.

96
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,769
我打算将马普尔小姐安置在法比安套房 夫人
I've put Miss Marple in the Fabian Suite, ma'm.

97
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:10,669
好主意
Good thinking.

98
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:14,139
简 这是朱丽叶・贝耶维 简直是我的一切
Jane, this is Juliet Bellever, who's simply everything to me,

99
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:19,150
护士 保镖 管家 也是忠实的朋友
nurse, dragon, watch-dog... and very faithful friend.

100
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:22,060
乔莉 晚饭吃什么 我饿死了
Jolly! What's for dinner? I'm starved.

101
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:27,569
凯洛格先生认为 食物中额外的蛋白质
As Mr. Kellogg approval, an excess of protein in the diet

102
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:31,069
会激发罪犯的犯罪意识
excites all the wrong instincts amongst with criminal intents

103
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:35,420
我们发现大麦是绝佳的替代品
We found in barley an excelent substitute.

104
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:38,670
- 是这样吧 马弗里克医生 - 确实
- Isn't that so, Dr. Maverick? - Indeed.

105
00:07:38,940 --> 00:07:41,870
我希望我们每周聚餐一次
I like us all to eat together once a week.

106
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:46,010
想让所有犯人感觉我们是一家人
I like all my charges to feel like they're part of the family.

107
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,120
我们确实是 亲爱的
And so we do, my dear.

108
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,350
他们真般配
They make a splendid couple.

109
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,069
我希望不是
I should hope not!

110
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,999
那是我继子 斯蒂文・雷斯塔瑞克
That's my stepson, Stephen Restarick.

111
00:07:57,010 --> 00:07:58,469
我第二任丈夫约翰尼的孩子
By my second husband, Johnny.

112
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,980
- 那个戏剧制作人 - 当然
- The theater producer. - Of course he is.

113
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:04,260
在这里万事皆可
All matter of waflles and strays under this roof.

114
00:08:04,310 --> 00:08:06,530
每个人都会犯错
Eveyone's allowed an error of judgement.

115
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:08,849
爸爸是你的 是吧 亲爱的
Dad was yours. Isn't that right, darling?

116
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:11,989
有什么好笑的
Not quite a laughing matter.

117
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:16,110
我妻子在戏剧评论中说斯蒂文是不可或缺的
Steven has made himself indispensible to my wife's dramatic review

118
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,990
卡莉・路易斯让我每年出演她的一部戏
Carrie Louise chooses me to stage a show for her every year.

119
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,770
为了鼓舞军队士气
Moral booster for the troops.

120
00:08:22,050 --> 00:08:25,020
你继承父亲的戏剧事业了吗 雷斯塔瑞克先生
Are you in the theater like your father, Mr. Restarick?

121
00:08:26,470 --> 00:08:28,000
我从事纺织业
I'm in fabrics,

122
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:29,479
软装饰
soft furnishing.

123
00:08:29,490 --> 00:08:31,010
让我不再淘气
Keeps me out of mischief.

124
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,089
但斯蒂维会在春天红透西区
But Stevie is going to storm the West End, in the spring,

125
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,170
是吧 亲爱的
aren't you, darling?

126
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:38,209
吉娜的丈夫呢
And Gina's husband?

127
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:41,620
一位叫瓦利・哈德的绅士 来自怀俄明
A gentleman called Wally Hudd. From Wyoming.

128
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:45,340
哈德先生非常喜欢烤鸡
Mr. Hudd has a great fondness for grilled chicken.

129
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,773
他和吉娜在诺曼底登陆那天相遇 
He and Gina met during D-Day. 

130
00:08:47,774 --> 00:08:48,580
你可以想象那个画面
You can imagine.

131
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,170
正相反 我觉得他们非常般配
On the contrary, I think they're admirably suited.

132
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:54,590
有什么好的战争故事 瓦利
Did you have a good war, Wally?

133
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,390
我没死
Well, it didn't kill me.

134
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,910
但也没变得更坚强
But it didn't make me stronger.

135
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,310
我能帮您吗
May I help you?

136
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:37,960
不 不
No! No,

137
00:09:40,010 --> 00:09:42,980
那场火灾真令人遗憾
such a pity, uh? The fire.

138
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,210
没错
Quite.

139
00:09:46,310 --> 00:09:47,830
几个月之后才恢复元气
Set us back some months.

140
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:52,420
- 我是艾德加・罗森 - 我叫简・马普尔
- Edgar Lawson. - Jane Marple.

141
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,340
我想也是
So I gather.

142
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:59,310
你...为卡莉・路易斯工作吗
Uh... You work for Carrie Louise?

143
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,200
为塞罗科尔德先生
For Mr Serrocold.

144
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:04,490
我是他的私人秘书
I'm his personal secretary.

145
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:08,450
- 听上去很重要 - 有时是
- Sounds terribly important. - Has its moments.

146
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,980
但...
But...

147
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:16,150
- 我能说个秘密吗 - 当然
- May I speak in confidence? - Of course.

148
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:17,980
您要发誓
Swear it, please.

149
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:21,229
我不想动摇他的地位
You see, I have no wish to compromise his position.

150
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,090
- 塞罗科尔德先生的吗 - 不
- Mr. Serrocold's? - No.

151
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,280
我父亲的
My father.

152
00:10:25,770 --> 00:10:28,370
其实我是
You see, I am, in fact,

153
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,350
温斯顿・丘吉尔的儿子
Winston Churchill's son.

154
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:36,530
是 看得出来
Yes, I think I do see.

155
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:40,040
他尽其所能帮助我 但他们监视我
He does what he can, but they spy on me.

156
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:41,750
总是这样
Always have done.

157
00:10:42,730 --> 00:10:44,529
还有...政治诽谤运动
And... the whispering campaign.

158
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:47,440
如果不是这该死的政治诽谤
If it wasn't for that damned whispering, you see?

159
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,629
有谁看见塞罗科尔德夫人了
Has anyone's seen Mrs. Serrocold?

160
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,670
我也奇怪呢
I was thinking the same thing.

161
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,930
这是她这周第二次忘记吃药了
It's the second time this week she forgot her tonic.

162
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,740
这个女人根本不在乎自己的健康
The woman has no head for her own safety.

163
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:00,930
塞罗科尔德夫人 米尔德里德小姐
Mrs. Serrocold? Miss Mildred?

164
