妈妈
Mommy?

165
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:08,890
- 她们在干什么 - 天哪 妈妈
- What is that? - Oh, gosh! Mommy!

166
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,690
妈妈
Mommy!

167
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:14,440
吉娜
Gina!

168
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:18,149
快回来 你会够不着底的
Come back this minute! You'll be out of your depth!

169
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,820
亲爱的 求求你
Honey, please!

170
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:21,460
你们也下来吧
Aren't you going to come in?

171
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:24,670
轻轻一跃 清醒一下
A quick leap. Wonderfully refreshing.

172
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:28,180
- 吉娜 - 闭上眼睛
- Gina! - Advert your eyes.

173
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:30,880
- 你也是 老兄 - 别这么叫我
- You too, bro. - Don't call me that!

174
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,000
你在想什么
What were you thinking of?

175
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,689
斯蒂文碰巧提到
It happens that Stephen mentioned that

176
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,920
潜水能治疗关节炎
a cool dive does wonders for arthritis.

177
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,749
你知道妈妈 总是第一个挑战自己
And you know mommy, always the first to the barricade.

178
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,509
- 但她几乎不会游泳 - 瞎说
- But she can hardly swim! - Oh, nonsense.

179
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,940
救命 救命
Help! Help!

180
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:02,289
现在高兴了 今天的混乱还不够多吗
Happy now? Caused sufficient chaos for one night?

181
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,429
别说了 蜜儿
Give me a rest, Mil.

182
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,589
我来了 我来了
I'm coming! I'm coming!

183
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,910
小心 刘易斯 水很深
Careful, Lewis, it does get deep there.

184
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:10,179
我来了 坚持住
I'm coming! Hang on!

185
00:12:10,190 --> 00:12:13,330
你怎么想 马普尔小姐 脑子犯抽了吧
What do they say, Miss Marple? Blood ran out?

186
00:12:17,020 --> 00:12:19,870
塞罗科尔德先生会游泳吗
Is he an able swimmer, Mr Serrocold?

187
00:12:19,950 --> 00:12:21,900
这儿就没个人真的会游泳吗
Can anyone here actually swim?

188
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,027
受不了了 你们就会光说不练
Very good, low lovers,

189
00:12:23,028 --> 00:12:24,769
我一个人去救他们 就算死了也算试过了
I'll rescue them myself or die trying.

190
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:25,548
你开玩笑吧
You won't do that.

191
00:12:25,549 --> 00:12:26,510
吉娜 你不许下去
Gina, don't you dare!

192
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:29,940
米尔德里德  那些小伙子是什么人
I say, Mildred, who are those young men?

193
00:12:35,370 --> 00:12:37,240
看来你的祈祷管用了 蜜儿
Looks like your prayers were answered, Mil.

194
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:43,493
亲爱的鲁思 我希望能够对你说
My dear Ruth, i had hoped to 

195
00:12:43,494 --> 00:12:46,560
你担心卡莉・路易斯的人身安全
dispel your concerns 

196
00:12:46,561 --> 00:12:47,480
完全是杞人忧天
over Carrie Louise's safety,

197
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,910
但是恐怕事与愿违
but I fear I can not.

198
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:53,510
她还是像以前那样开朗阳光
She has the same bright spirit as ever,

199
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:56,059
但正如你先前所暗示的那样
but there may, as you suggested,

200
00:12:56,070 --> 00:12:59,780
斯托尼盖特可能真的暗潮涌动
be dark forces at play here in Stonygates.

201
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:03,850
吉娜正如你描述的那样迷人
Gina is as bewitching as you say.

202
00:13:04,210 --> 00:13:05,320
家中的继子 
Certainly, the stepson, 

203
00:13:05,321 --> 00:13:08,280
斯蒂文・雷斯塔瑞克也发现了这一点
Stephen Restarick, finds her so,

204
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:13,130
但她的丈夫却对这一切视若无睹 漠不关心
while her american husband looks away, as if indifferent.

205
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:21,710
还有艾德加・罗森
And then there is Edgar Lawson.

206
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:27,730
他与周围格格不入
He is maladjusted, certainly.

207
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:31,720
除此之外 艾德加・罗森还有一点不对劲
But there is something else a little wrong about Edgar Lawson.

208
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:38,160
但这跟卡莉・路易斯有什么关系 
There what is, and it is and when it touches Carrie Louise,

209
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:40,620
我还说不好
I can not yet say.

210
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:07,590
那件事一定吓到你了
It must have been a terrible shock for you. 

211
00:14:07,590 --> 00:14:09,239
我是指 那场火灾
The fire, I mean.

212
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:10,171
我书房的那次吗
In my study? 

213
00:14:10,172 --> 00:14:12,510
没那回事 只是场意外
Oh, no, no. That was an accident.

214
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:13,610
只是
It's just ...

215
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,861
这件事千万不要
Promise you won't breathe a word 

216
00:14:14,862 --> 00:14:17,500
让可怜的刘易斯知道 但是...
of this to my poor Lewis, but ...

217
00:14:17,780 --> 00:14:20,090
我的英雄
Oh, the hero of the hour!

218
00:14:20,340 --> 00:14:22,371
阿尔巴特・安东尼
Albator, Anthony!

219
00:14:22,372 --> 00:14:23,440
夫人
Madam.

220
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:26,609
八次盗窃 四次入侵民宅
Eight cons for burglary, four for breaking and entering,

221
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:28,869
还有更多我数都数不过来的罪行
and more gravous harm than I have fingers and toes to count,

222
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:32,579
但是昨天晚上 这位绅士救了我的命
but last night, this gentleman saved my life.

223
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:34,099
虽然场面挺狼狈的
All it takes is a little dignity,

224
00:14:34,110 --> 00:14:36,540
还得跟内政局解释才行
though try and say that to the Home Office.

225
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:38,689
这位是惠特斯特布尔・欧尼斯特
And this is Whitstable Ernest.

226
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:40,279
你的西红柿长势好吗
How are your tomatoes prospering?

227
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:41,620
都熟透了 夫人
Ripe as prune, ma'am.

228
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:43,890
想尝一个吗 夫人
Care to try one, madam?

229
00:14:44,410 --> 00:14:45,740
好的 谢谢
Very nice. Thank you.

230
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:48,549
塞罗科尔德先生现在恢复了吧
Mr. Serrocold's fully recovered from his paddle, I hope?

231
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:51,640
好多了 今早乘头班车去伦敦了
Oh, quite. Off to London in the first train this morning.

232
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:52,628
是生意上的事吧
Business, I expect.

233
00:14:52,629 --> 00:14:53,389
没错
That's right.

234
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,799
欧尼斯特一度对金融很有兴趣
Ernest once took a great interest in finantial matters.

235
00:14:56,810 --> 00:14:59,299
就是有点过头了 是吧 夫人
Yes, got a bit ahead of myself, didn't I, ma'am?

236
00:14:59,310 --> 00:15:01,829
他曾未经人同意就拿别人的钱投资
He used to invest other people's money without their permission.

237
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:04,949
看得出来 你是个园艺能手
You have green fingers, I see.

238
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:07,260
谢谢夸奖 很高兴能派上用场
Thank you. And happily free to use them.

239
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:10,120
这里湖光山色 还有这么漂亮的园子
Lakeside view, a excellent piece of garden.

240
00:15:10,540 --> 00:15:12,780
没有比这更好的休闲地点了
Can't think a more pleasant place to telax on.

241
00:15:12,790 --> 00:15:15,870
你这么一说 我都想加入你们了
Put like that, I feel I might join you.

242
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,240
这边的大门永远都是敞开的
Well, there's always room for one more.

243
00:15:19,570 --> 00:15:21,420
塞罗科尔德太太
Mrs. Serrocold?

244
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:22,509
乔莉什么事
Jolly?

245
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:24,549
有一位绅士要见您
There's a gentleman to see you.

246
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,960
我马上就来
I'll be along in a moment.

247
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:34,750
克里斯提安
Christian!

248
00:15:36,590 --> 00:15:39,352
不是你想见的人对吧
Not whom you were expecting?

249
00:15:39,353 --> 00:15:41,010
我不知道你要来
I didn't know.

250
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:43,460
你还是老样子 总是神神秘秘的
Wrapped as you were, in such mistery!

251
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:46,211
胡说 我昨晚跟刘易斯说过了
Nonsense. I told Lewis last night.

252
00:15:46,212 --> 00:15:47,609
他没告诉你吗
Didn't he tell you?

253
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:48,799
也许吧
Oh, perhaps he did.

254
00:15:48,810 --> 00:15:51,540
我让乔莉给你安排奇尔・哈迪的房间
I'll get Jolly to prepare Kier Hardie's room.

255
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:52,949
简 很抱歉
Oh, Jane, I'm so sorry.

256
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:54,729
我来跟你介绍克里斯提安 
Allow me to present Christian.

257
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:56,286
我的另一个继子 
My other stepson, 

258
00:15:56,287 --> 00:15:58,799
他父亲是我已故的第一任丈夫
by way of my late and beloved first husband.

259
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,109
我明白了 虽然有点复杂
I see. Well, I think I do.

260
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:02,049
女士
Madam.

261
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:04,990
我希望你这次不会那么快离开
I hope you don't deserting us too soon this time.

262
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:07,279
至少呆到周末好吗
At least stay for the weekend?

263
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:09,950
我来这儿是打算跟刘易斯谈事情的
I was hoping to have a word with Lewis.

264
00:16:10,580 --> 00:16:15,339
都是生意上的事 很乏味的
Business matter. All very tedious.

265
00:16:15,350 --> 00:16:18,690
他现在不在 那你干脆愉快地留下吧
Well, he's not here, so you'll jolly have to wait!

266
00:16:18,690 --> 00:16:19,710
恭敬不如从命
So much the better.

267
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:22,370
来 我们带你看看园子去
Come, let us show you the garden.

268
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:26,440
今天天气多好啊
Such a lovely day.

269
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:29,610
他们应该跟我商量一下的
They might have consulted me.

270
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:32,140
罗森先生
Mr. Lawson!

271
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:34,800
我是塞罗科尔德先生的私人秘书
I'm Mr. Serrocold's p-personal secretary,

272
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:36,889
所以 如果事情真的这么紧急
so, Gulbrandsen should have come to me,

273
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,477
古尔布兰德森应该来问我的
if it's all so urgent.

274
00:16:38,478 --> 00:16:39,200
没错
Indeed.

275
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:41,900
他们把我当傻瓜
They take me for a fool.

276
00:16:42,650 --> 00:16:45,260
但是我已经知道了 那才是重点
But I know. That's the point.

277
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,430
你知道什么
What do you know?

278
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:49,820
他是恶魔附身
He has the devil in him.

279
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:54,239
谁 古尔布兰德森先生还是...你父亲
Who? Mr. Gulbrandsen or... your father?

280
00:16:54,250 --> 00:16:55,279
你等着瞧吧
Just you wait and see.

281
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:56,660
别烦她
Leave her alone.

282
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:59,550
你在监视我吗
Spying on me?

283
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,380
看不出这位老夫人想安静会儿吗 快走开
Can't you see the old dame wants some peace? Go on and splt.

284
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:05,060
这就走
Gladly.

285
00:17:09,930 --> 00:17:12,260
你手上拿的是咖啡吗
Is that coffee you have there?

286
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:14,739
能给我喝一点吗 压压惊
Perhaps you could spare a drop. My nerves!

287
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:16,246
这咖啡很浓
I make it pretty strong.

288
00:17:16,247 --> 00:17:18,260
我就喜欢喝浓咖啡
Well, that's the way I like it.

289
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:24,239
来一杯乔[咖啡] 你们美国人是这么说的吗
A cup of Joe. Isn't that the way you Americans call it?

290
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,080
还只是电影里这么演
Or is that just for the pictures?

291
00:17:27,330 --> 00:17:28,780
我有时候很好奇
You know, I sometimes wonder 

292
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:31,889
乔到底是个人 还是什么东西
who or what Joe is.

293
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:36,759
不管他是谁 但愿上帝保佑他
Well ... God bless him, whoever he is.

294
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:38,030
干杯
Cheers.

295
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:46,800
每当从这儿看出去 看到这些景象
You know, when I look out, on all this, 

296
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:50,039
我就有点想念我的紫菀园
I begin to feel a little homesick for my asters.

297
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,390
我也有同感
You and me, both.

298
00:17:52,020 --> 00:17:53,409
你也种紫菀吗
You have asters?

299
00:17:53,410 --> 00:17:55,030
不是 我...
Oh, no, I... hmm.

300
00:17:56,490 --> 00:17:58,063
你是指思乡
Homesick.

301
00:17:58,064 --> 00:17:59,350
是的
Yeah.

302
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:02,809
思乡只有一种解药
Well, there's only one known cure for that.

303
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,299
小公主才不会懂这些
Try telling that to princess.

304
00:18:04,299 --> 00:18:06,299
我能给她什么呢
What have I got to give her?

305
00:18:14,990 --> 00:18:16,340
你好 这里是斯托尼盖特
Hello. Stonygates.

306
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:19,000
很好 先生
Very good, sir.

307
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:22,220
不用了 我已经通知过园丁了
There's no need. I've already indormed the groundsman.

308
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:25,430
我会亲自确认的 再见
I'll see to it myself. Goodbye.

309
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:27,855
是塞罗科尔德先生吗
Was that Mr. Serrocold?

310
00:18:27,856 --> 00:18:28,830
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

311
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,789
他会如预计的四点二十七分到家
He'll be home in the 04:27, as planned.

312
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:35,799
也许我可以开车去车站接他
Perhaps I might drive up and meet him from the station?

313
00:18:35,810 --> 00:18:37,450
他想走着回来
He prefers to walk.

314
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:41,360
很好 贝耶维小姐
Very good ... Miss Bellever.

315
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:43,630
我去看看晚饭准备好了没
I should see about dinner.

316
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:46,580
马普尔小姐
Miss Marple.

317
00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:49,680
古尔布兰德森先生
Oh! Mr. Gulbrandsen!

318
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:52,140
我刚想去休息一会
Just off for a little lie down.

319
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,940
那么别因为我搅了您的雅兴
Well, don't let me keep you.

320
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,489
马普尔小姐 您已经认识卡莉・路易斯...
Miss Marple, you've known Carrie-Louise ...

321
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,849
大半辈子了 真是难以置信啊
Oh, most of my life, would you believe?

322
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:02,400
你觉得她怎么样
How do you find her?

323
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:05,459
永远的理想主义者
As great an idealist as ever.

324
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:07,440
也许是因为
Maybe she does not 

325
00:19:07,441 --> 00:19:12,170
她还没有领教过世事的残酷
appreciate the evil there is in the world

326
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,040
跟我说说 她健康情况如何
Tell me, how is her health?

327
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:18,010
我看起来觉得挺好
She seems to me well enough.

328
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:19,799
就是有点关节炎
Appart from the arthritis.

329
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:21,110
她的心脏呢
And her heart?

330
00:19:21,950 --> 00:19:23,320
她的心脏够强壮吗
Is her heart strong?

331
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:27,850
很强壮 古尔布兰德森先生
As far as one can tell, Mr Gulbrandsen.

332
00:19:29,030 --> 00:19:30,670
晚饭时再见
Until supper time.

333
00:19:30,790 --> 00:19:33,800
祝您睡眠愉快
Enjoy your... shut eye.

334
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:19,470
希望卡莉・路易斯不会知道...
Let's hope to spare Carrie Louise from knowledge ...

335
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:25,580
