She spoke only to decline the offer of prayers..."

1204
01:11:13,360 --> 01:11:14,430
你在哪找到的
Where did you find that?

1205
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:17,370
今早 在吉娜的房间里
In Gina's room, this morning.

1206
01:11:18,310 --> 01:11:21,880
凯瑟琳・埃尔斯沃思是吉娜的生母 对吧
Katherine Ellsworth was Gina's birthmother, wasn't she?

1207
01:11:21,920 --> 01:11:23,280
是
Yes.

1208
01:11:26,160 --> 01:11:28,830
可以从她女儿身上看到同样的冲动
And the same urges can be seen in the daughter.

1209
01:11:29,650 --> 01:11:34,189
我告诉过她 吉娜就是神秘的投毒者
I told her, Gina is our mystery poisoner

1210
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:37,104
还有 昨晚她弄的那个
and... last night's ridiculous 

1211
01:11:37,105 --> 01:11:39,719
金黄色发型真是滑稽
carry on with that blond hairdo,

1212
01:11:39,730 --> 01:11:41,991
使她和那个女凶手看起来很像 
making herself look like that murderess, 

1213
01:11:41,992 --> 01:11:42,960
让我妈妈心烦
to upset mummy

1214
01:11:43,240 --> 01:11:48,240
简直就是... 一个公开的忏悔
was nothing less than... a public confession.

1215
01:11:48,290 --> 01:11:50,039
我承认现在还不清楚
I admit I'm at a loss to know

1216
01:11:50,050 --> 01:11:52,950
吉娜是怎么知道这一切的 但...
how Gina came to learn of all this, but uh ...

1217
01:11:54,010 --> 01:11:56,295
可能是有人故意把这张报纸
perhaps someone put the newspaper there 

1218
01:11:56,296 --> 01:11:58,009
放在那边让她看见的
for her to discover.

1219
01:11:58,020 --> 01:11:59,530
不可能
That's impossible.

1220
01:11:59,730 --> 01:12:01,860
没人知道 就连刘易斯也不知道
No-one knew. Not even Lewis.

1221
01:12:01,870 --> 01:12:04,620
只有我自己和米尔德里德
Only myself and Mildred.

1222
01:12:08,540 --> 01:12:09,790
米尔德里德
Mildred?

1223
01:12:11,340 --> 01:12:15,840
你怎么能这样 她是你姐姐
How could you? She's your sister!

1224
01:12:21,240 --> 01:12:25,740
你总是说 我们应该分享
You always said...we should share.

1225
01:12:26,830 --> 01:12:28,420
但她不肯
Well, she won't.

1226
01:12:30,020 --> 01:12:32,390
她不与我分享
She won't share.

1227
01:12:33,140 --> 01:12:34,720
从未有过
She never did.

1228
01:12:35,430 --> 01:12:36,940
不仅是你
Not you.

1229
01:12:39,270 --> 01:12:41,090
她夺走了所有人
Not anybody.

1230
01:12:48,440 --> 01:12:52,200
我可怜的吉娜
Oh, my...my poor darling Gina.

1231
01:12:52,990 --> 01:12:54,690
你觉得她在责怪我吗
Do you think she blames me?

1232
01:12:55,430 --> 01:12:57,950
你觉得昨天晚上她故意穿成那样
D'you think last night she was trying to hurt me

1233
01:12:58,430 --> 01:13:00,569
是对我这么多年一直对她隐瞒的报复吗
for keeping it from her all these years?

1234
01:13:00,580 --> 01:13:02,299
也可能为了伤害自己
Or hurt herself.

1235
01:13:02,310 --> 01:13:04,419
我一定要去找她 跟她谈
I must go to her, speak to her.

1236
01:13:04,430 --> 01:13:09,130
卡莉・路易斯 也许你应该两边都谈谈
Carrie Louise, perhaps you should speak to them both.

1237
01:13:09,670 --> 01:13:13,670
也许这样你才能平息这多年的阴影
Together, perhaps you could lay this particular ghost to rest.

1238
01:13:28,190 --> 01:13:30,340
我还是先喝完茶吧
I think I'll finish my tea first.

1239
01:13:31,720 --> 01:13:34,980
我想若世界上没有那么多秘密
I think we would all sleep a lot better in our beds

1240
01:13:36,230 --> 01:13:39,450
也许我们晚上就能安然入眠
if there weren't quite so many secrets in the world.

1241
01:13:42,320 --> 01:13:44,030
你了解多少了
How much do you know?

1242
01:13:44,120 --> 01:13:46,010
我并不确定
If I was quite sure... 

1243
01:13:46,011 --> 01:13:47,900
我知道你已经清楚了
Oh, I think you're sure.

1244
01:13:49,530 --> 01:13:51,200
你想要我怎么做
What do you want me to do?

1245
01:13:55,080 --> 01:13:59,710
做你唯一能做的 去跟探长先生说
The only thing you can do. Talk to the inspector.

1246
01:14:02,070 --> 01:14:04,350
等我喝完这杯茶
Just as soon as I finish my tea.

1247
01:14:14,520 --> 01:14:17,209
是约翰尼・雷斯塔瑞克让我想到的这点
It was Johnny Restarick that gave me the idea.

1248
01:14:17,220 --> 01:14:20,630
把这间屋子不看作一间会客厅
To think of this room, not just a drawing room ...

1249
01:14:20,910 --> 01:14:23,150
可以的话把窗帘向左拉一些
Oh, a little to the left, if you wouldn't mind.

1250
01:14:24,210 --> 01:14:25,309
就这样
Just so. Um ...

1251
01:14:25,320 --> 01:14:27,085
不是简单的一间会客厅 
Not just a drawing room, 

1252
01:14:27,086 --> 01:14:28,850
而是一个摆满道具的场景
but as a stage set.

1253
01:14:29,060 --> 01:14:29,960
就是这样
There.

1254
01:14:30,200 --> 01:14:32,290
一个戏剧晚会
An evening of dramatics.

1255
01:14:33,610 --> 01:14:35,409
向平常一样的出入口
The usual entrances and exits.

1256
01:14:35,420 --> 01:14:39,159
当然 还有后场 也就是外面的平台
And backstage, of course, outside, on the terrace.

1257
01:14:39,170 --> 01:14:42,460
包括我在内的观众坐在这
The audience, myself included, sat here,

1258
01:14:42,660 --> 01:14:45,260
被一个把戏所吸引
audient by a conjuring trick.

1259
01:14:45,720 --> 01:14:47,289
他们利用了"魔镜"
They do it with mirrors.

1260
01:14:47,300 --> 01:14:50,600
- "魔镜" - 这不是行话吗
- Mirrors? - Oh, isn't that the common slang?

1261
01:14:50,690 --> 01:14:53,900
一些很简单的误导行为
A few, simple acts of misdirection.

1262
01:14:54,060 --> 01:14:55,769
首先是停电
First, the power cut.

1263
01:14:55,780 --> 01:14:57,969
你认为停电是有人故意为之的
You think the lights were meant to go out.

1264
01:14:57,980 --> 01:14:59,550
我相当确定
Oh, I'm quite sure of it.

1265
01:14:59,910 --> 01:15:02,699
你记得白天的那次断电吧
You recall the power cut early in the day,

1266
01:15:02,710 --> 01:15:06,410
就是他们晚饭前用灯来试验的那次
set off by the spotlights that were being tested before supper.

1267
01:15:07,190 --> 01:15:11,300
那时候保险丝就被设置好
The fuse box was then primed to blow a second time

1268
01:15:11,390 --> 01:15:15,040
以待在会客厅的线路过载时再次跳断
when the circuit of the drawing room was overloaded.

1269
01:15:17,290 --> 01:15:19,859
- 断电了 - 线路跳断了
- Oh, block. - Wires on the blink.

1270
01:15:19,870 --> 01:15:21,649
我去看看保险丝
I'll go and check the fuse box.

1271
01:15:21,660 --> 01:15:23,530
是那个美国人吗 瓦利・哈德
The north-american? Wally Hudd?

1272
01:15:24,100 --> 01:15:27,600
这将我引向了第二个误导
Oh. Which brings me to the second misdirection.

1273
01:15:29,890 --> 01:15:31,360
能不能...
Oh. Would you mind?

1274
01:15:33,640 --> 01:15:35,380
- 暗门 - 对
- The hidden door. - Yes.

1275
01:15:35,470 --> 01:15:40,469
我们判断这边是凶手的第二个出口
Now, here we deduce, was the killers second exit.

1276
01:15:40,580 --> 01:15:44,290
当然停电的时候 没人知道发生了什么
And, with the lights out, of course, nobody can be sure of anything,

1277
01:15:44,470 --> 01:15:48,190
使得你有了更多的嫌疑人 探长先生
leaving you, Inspector, with a far wider cast of suspects.

1278
01:15:48,880 --> 01:15:52,369
如果这暗门与谋杀根本无关呢
What if the the door had nothing to do with the murder?

1279
01:15:52,380 --> 01:15:56,590
如果凶手用更加简单的方法出去了呢
Hm? What if the killer made a far simpler escape?

1280
01:15:57,040 --> 01:16:00,829
永远不要低估那些显而易见的事实 探长先生
Never underestimate the power of the obvious, Inspector.

1281
01:16:00,840 --> 01:16:02,460
确实 那么...
Indeed. So ...

1282
01:16:04,760 --> 01:16:05,870
请坐
Would you ...

1283
01:16:06,240 --> 01:16:07,100
现在
Now,

1284
01:16:08,010 --> 01:16:12,720
那两个人从落地窗走到平台上
two men step through the french windows onto the terrace.

1285
01:16:12,960 --> 01:16:17,070
但我们事实上看到的是什么
But what do we see? What do we actually see?

1286
01:16:17,740 --> 01:16:19,600
当然 有艾德加・罗森
Edgar Lawson, of course,

1287
01:16:20,140 --> 01:16:23,300
但塞罗科尔德先生去哪里了
but what became of Mr. Serrocold?

1288
01:16:23,650 --> 01:16:24,799
我们听见了他的声音
We heard him.

1289
01:16:24,810 --> 01:16:26,590
- 谢谢 塞罗科尔德先生 - 艾德加
- Thank you, Mr Serrocold. - Edgar!

1290
01:16:28,060 --> 01:16:30,459
- 不许动 - 够了
- Nobody move! - That's enough.

1291
01:16:30,470 --> 01:16:31,780
另一个把戏
Another trick.

1292
01:16:31,830 --> 01:16:34,419
艾德加是在模仿...
Edgar was simply mimicking the voice of ...

1293
01:16:34,430 --> 01:16:36,450
- 刘易斯・塞罗科尔德的声音 - 对
- Lewis Serrocold! - Mm-hm.

1294
01:16:36,500 --> 01:16:38,660
凶手根本不需要花任何时间
The killer would have taken no time at all.

1295
01:16:38,750 --> 01:16:42,120
比你手下一分零七秒更快
No more than your sargeant's one minute and seven seconds.

1296
01:16:50,130 --> 01:16:53,509
动机呢 我从没见过那么爱自己妻子的男人
But why? I never saw a man so devoted to his wife.

1297
01:16:53,520 --> 01:16:54,500
确实如此
Quite.

1298
01:16:54,920 --> 01:16:59,559
但我们怎么知道是否真的有个投毒者
But how do we know there really was a poisoner?

1299
01:16:59,570 --> 01:17:01,000
看看现有的证据
Look at the evidence.

1300
01:17:01,010 --> 01:17:05,350
卡莉・路易斯的关节炎仅仅是个巧合
Carrie Louise's arthritis was a coincidence, nothing more.

1301
01:17:05,510 --> 01:17:06,819
她用的药
And her tonic,

1302
01:17:06,830 --> 01:17:10,830
在十一点时被混入了极少量的砒霜
mixed at eleventh hour with very few drops of arsenic,

1303
01:17:10,910 --> 01:17:13,039
不是为了杀死卡莉・路易斯
intended not for Carrie Louise,

1304
01:17:13,050 --> 01:17:16,060
而是想让你和你的同事去发现
but for you and your colleagues to discover.

1305
01:17:17,570 --> 01:17:20,750
另外当塞罗科尔德先生在检查尸体时
A few words were then added to the letter

1306
01:17:20,760 --> 01:17:23,210
他在信中加了一些字
when Mr. Serrocold examined his body.

1307
01:17:23,490 --> 01:17:25,479
我有理由相信
I have reason to believe

1308
01:17:25,490 --> 01:17:29,340
她正慢慢地被人下药毒害
she is being slowly and cold-bloodedly poisoned.

1309
01:17:29,810 --> 01:17:32,300
我最初有此怀疑是在...
I first suspected it when...

1310
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:37,560
这样信的意思就变了许多
And the meaning was quite altered.

1311
01:17:37,870 --> 01:17:41,480
所以并没有人想要毒害塞罗科尔德夫人
So, there never was any plot to poison Mrs. Serrocold.

1312
01:17:41,610 --> 01:17:43,190
是的 探长先生
No, Inspector.

1313
01:17:43,200 --> 01:17:46,300
我知道约翰尼也如此怀疑
And I'm sure Johnny suspected as much.

1314
01:17:46,350 --> 01:17:47,669
因为很奇怪地
Hence his rather odd desire

1315
01:17:47,680 --> 01:17:51,880
他在死前一直想要剪卡莉・路易斯的指甲
to trim Carrie Louise's fingernails a few minutes before he died.

1316
01:17:52,340 --> 01:17:54,869
剪下的指甲样本能很快证明
A sample of nail-clipping would soon have proven

1317
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:57,019
她的血液中并无毒素
there was no arsenic in her bloostream.

1318
01:17:57,030 --> 01:18:00,290
- 但他如何知道... - 就在花园里
- But how could he possibly... - There, in the garden,

1319
01:18:00,340 --> 01:18:01,880
在去房子的路上
on his way up to the house,

1320
01:18:01,930 --> 01:18:04,920
他看了一眼那后台
he had a glimpse of the backstage, as it were.

1321
01:18:05,500 --> 01:18:09,970
尽管起了雾 但有枪声和脚印
Even through the fog. Gunshots. And footsteps.

1322
01:18:10,840 --> 01:18:13,939
当他如此友好地对待欧尼斯特时
And when Johnny befriended Ernest at the facility,

1323
01:18:13,950 --> 01:18:15,649
我认为他那时就开始就一片一片地
I'm sure he began to piece together

1324
01:18:15,660 --> 01:18:18,650
拼凑起这个毒害骗局背后的情况
the hidding story behind the poisoning hoax.

1325
01:18:19,010 --> 01:18:21,689
在欧尼斯特房间里的那些东西
as for all those treats in Ernest's room

1326
01:18:21,700 --> 01:18:25,540
威士忌 钥匙 生蚝
the single malt whiskey, the keys, the oysters ...

1327
01:18:26,200 --> 01:18:27,710
不是偷来的
.. They weren't stolen.

1328
01:18:27,830 --> 01:18:30,480
而是刘易斯・塞罗科尔德送他的
They were gifts from Lewis Serrocold.

1329
01:18:31,150 --> 01:18:36,129
是一个利用自己高超的诈骗挪用技巧
Grateful tokens to a man whose rare talent for fraud and

1330
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:40,219
来挽回信用基金损失财产的人得到的奖赏
embezzlement had helped restore the fallen fortune of Gulbrandsen Trust

1331
01:18:40,230 --> 01:18:41,470
但为什么
But why?

1332
01:18:42,210 --> 01:18:44,299
那样一个正直的绅士
An upstanding gentleman like that.

1333
01:18:44,310 --> 01:18:46,700
"一切都为了爱"
"The things we do for love."

1334
01:18:47,480 --> 01:18:49,230
是不是这样
Wasn't it like that, 

1335
01:18:49,231 --> 01:18:50,230
塞罗科尔德先生
the way you put it, Mr Serrocold?

1336
01:18:52,570 --> 01:18:53,850
不错
Quite right.

1337
01:18:55,890 --> 01:18:57,140
简
Jane.

1338
01:18:59,470 --> 01:19:01,938
克里斯提安・古尔布兰德森
Christian Gulbrandsen 

1339
01:19:01,939 --> 01:19:03,789
发现了你的经济问题
had discovered your slide into

1340
01:19:03,800 --> 01:19:07,580
并打算揭发此事
financial corruption and sought to expose it.

1341
01:19:09,100 --> 01:19:12,228
但因为他对卡莉・路易斯的感情
Only his affection for Carrie Louise 

1342
01:19:12,229 --> 01:19:13,480
使他停下了脚步
gave him pause.

1343
01:19:14,220 --> 01:19:16,820
他问我"她的心脏是否强壮" 
Was her heart strong, you see.

1344
01:19:17,310 --> 01:19:19,109
你肯定知道
You must have known,

1345
01:19:19,120 --> 01:19:20,756
就在七周前
he was onto you, 

1346
01:19:20,757 --> 01:19:22,720
他把受托人都召集到斯托尼盖特的时候 
the last time Christian came to Stonygates.

1347
01:19:23,240 --> 01:19:26,330
你就知道他是冲你来的
When the Trustees convened, seven weeks ago,

1348
01:19:26,800 --> 01:19:29,640
那时你就开始构思你的计划了 对吗
that's when you conceived your plan, wasn't it?

1349
01:19:30,240 --> 01:19:31,710
先是那场火
First, the fire,

1350
01:19:31,950 --> 01:19:33,889
不是电路故障起火
started not by faulty wiring,

1351
01:19:33,900 --> 01:19:34,886
而是你的同谋 
but by your accomplice, 

1352
01:19:34,887 --> 01:19:36,860
惠特斯特布尔・欧尼斯特纵的火
Whitstable Ernest.

1353
01:19:37,520 --> 01:19:40,450
他藏在暗门
Concealed behind the hidden door.

1354
01:19:42,330 --> 01:19:45,560
只是留下了一些汽油滴下的痕迹
Only he left a few tale trail drops of petroleum.

1355
01:19:45,760 --> 01:19:48,900
因此我们会在那里闻到柴油的味道
The smell we talked of diesel on the floor boards.

1356
01:19:49,370 --> 01:19:52,309
那场火真正的目的
The real target of those flames

1357
01:19:52,320 --> 01:19:55,850
并不是你妻子的照片或是遗嘱
wasn't your wife's photographs or even her will,

1358
01:19:56,590 --> 01:20:00,700
而是档案柜里的账目记录
it was the accounts records housed in the filing cabinet.

1359
01:20:01,640 --> 01:20:03,310
这为你争取了不少时间
That bought you some time,

1360
01:20:03,780 --> 01:20:06,470
但你知道 克里斯提安不会这样放过你
but you knew Christian couldn't be put off forever.

1361
01:20:07,290 --> 01:20:11,570
你就打算在他下次来斯托尼盖特时杀他灭口
And so you were ready to silence him when he next came up to Stonygates

1362
01:20:12,550 --> 01:20:15,209
这个改造工厂花光了我们所有积蓄
The reform facility ate up all we had.

1363
01:20:15,220 --> 01:20:17,740
那些地产 还有那些无休止的特权
The buildings. The endless privileges.

1364
01:20:19,880 --> 01:20:21,040
我只有这样...
It was the only way ...

1365
01:20:21,670 --> 01:20:23,450
我已经把所有东西都砸了进去
I poured everything in it.

1366
01:20:24,270 --> 01:20:25,820
信托基金
The Trust.

1367
01:20:26,170 --> 01:20:27,720
我自己的财产
My own fortune.

1368
01:20:29,510 --> 01:20:31,530
这是最后一搏了
It was the last resort.

1369
01:20:31,930 --> 01:20:33,590
你也明白 不是吗
You see that, don't you?

1370
01:20:34,730 --> 01:20:37,450
这是我能唯一想到的 让你开心点的方法了
It was the only way I knew to make you happy.

1371
01:20:38,420 --> 01:20:40,010
你若发现...
If you found out...

1372
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:46,690
你不必向我证明你如何爱我
You didn't have to prove yourself to me.

1373
01:20:47,280 --> 01:20:49,830
